<subSubSection pageId="16" pageNumber="17" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="16.[151,1437,1233,1618]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1341,1366]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Remarks.</emphasis>
The species is very rare and only known from three coastal localities in 
<collectingCountry box="[1157,1242,1341,1366]" name="Finland" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Finland</collectingCountry>
(
<emphasis box="[1261,1280,1342,1365]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">N</emphasis>
: Hanko, 
<emphasis box="[1388,1429,1342,1365]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Om</emphasis>
: Kokkola, 
<emphasis box="[269,317,1377,1402]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Oba</emphasis>
: Oulu) and two localities in Russian Fennoscandia. In 
<collectingCountry box="[1005,1094,1377,1402]" name="Finland" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Finland</collectingCountry>
, it is classified as critically endangered (
<bibRefCitation author="Paukkunen, J." box="[296,493,1413,1438]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" pagination="529 - 544" refId="ref60457" refString="Paukkunen, J. (2010) Stinging wasps. In: Rassi, P., Hyvarinen, E., Juslen, A. &amp; Mannerkoski, I. (Eds.), The 2010 Red List of Finnish Species. Finnish Ministry of Environment &amp; Finnish Environment Institute, Helsinki, pp. 529 - 544." type="book chapter" year="2010">Paukkunen 2010</bibRefCitation>
). The species was erroneously synonymized with 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Soon" authorityYear="2004" box="[1068,1183,1413,1438]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Holopyga" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fervida">
<emphasis box="[1068,1183,1413,1438]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">H. fervida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="Trautmann, W." box="[1230,1436,1413,1438]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" refId="ref63572" refString="Trautmann, W. (1927) Die Goldwespen Europas. Uschman, Weimar, 194 pp. + 2 pls." type="book" year="1927">Trautmann (1927)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Linsenmaier, W." box="[198,413,1449,1474]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" pagination="1 - 110" refId="ref58473" refString="Linsenmaier, W. (1951) Die europaischen Chrysididen (Hymenoptera). Versuch einer naturlichen Ordnung mit Diagnosen. Mitteilungen der Schweizerischen Entomologischen Gesellschaft, 24, 1 - 110." type="journal article" year="1951">Linsenmaier (1951</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Linsenmaier, W." box="[424,484,1449,1474]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" pagination="1 - 232" refId="ref58506" refString="Linsenmaier, W. (1959) Revision der Familie Chrysididae (Hymenoptera) mit besonderer Brucksichtigung der europaischen Spezies. Mitteilungen der Schweizerischen Entomologischen Gesellschaft, 32, 1 - 232." type="journal article" year="1959">1959</bibRefCitation>
). However, 
<bibRefCitation author="Linsenmaier, W." box="[619,841,1449,1474]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" pagination="133 - 158" refId="ref58569" refString="Linsenmaier, W. (1987) Revision der Familie Chrysididae (Hymenoptera). 4. Teil. Mitteilungen der Schweizerischen Entomologischen Gesellschaft, 60, 133 - 158." type="journal article" year="1987">Linsenmaier (1987)</bibRefCitation>
later reinstated it as a valid species.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="16.[151,1437,1233,1618]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">
<bibRefCitation author="Dahlbom, A. G." box="[199,385,1485,1510]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" refId="ref53528" refString="Dahlbom, A. G. (1854) Hymenoptera Europaea praecipue borealia, formis typicis nonnullis specierum generumve Exoticorum aut Extraneorum propter nexum systematicum associatis, per familias, genera, species et varietates disposita atque descripta. 2. Chrysis in sensu Linnaeano. Friedrich Nicolai, Berlin, xxiv + 412 pp. + 12 pls. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 15890" type="book" year="1854">Dahlbom (1854)</bibRefCitation>
described the species as 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Dahlbom" authorityYear="1854" box="[664,927,1485,1510]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Hedychrum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="metallicum">
<emphasis box="[664,927,1485,1510]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Hedychrum metallicum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
on the basis of 
<specimenCount box="[1102,1256,1485,1510]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" type="generic">one specimen</specimenCount>
collected by 
<collectorName pageId="16" pageNumber="17">W. Nylander</collectorName>
from 
<collectingCountry box="[325,411,1521,1546]" name="Finland" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Finland</collectingCountry>
in 
<date box="[447,587,1521,1546]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" value="1844-07-27">
<collectingDate box="[447,587,1521,1546]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" value="1844-07-27">27.VII.1844</collectingDate>
</date>
. 
<collectorName box="[599,643,1521,1546]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">The</collectorName>
<typeStatus box="[650,748,1521,1546]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">holotype</typeStatus>
is a small male, and it is deposited in MZH in 
<collectorName box="[1280,1375,1521,1546]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Helsinki</collectorName>
(
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 2–5" captionStartId="15.[151,264,1886,1909]" captionTargetBox="[169,1410,197,1855]" captionTargetId="figure-91@15.[169,1410,195,1855]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURES 2–5. 2) Holotype of Hedychrum metallicum Dahlbom, 1854 (= Holopyga metallica (Dahlbom, 1854)). 3) Lectotype of Hedychrum cupreum Dahlbom, 1845 (= Hedychridium cupreum (Dahlbom, 1845)). 4) Lectotype of Chrysis succincta var. virideocincta Trautmann, 1927 (= Chrysis bicolor Lepeletier de Saint Fargeau, 1806). 5) Holotype of Chrysis succincta var. westerlundi Trautmann, 1927 (= Chrysis westerlundi Trautmann, 1927). Scale 1 mm. Photos: Paolo Rosa (3) and Pekka Malinen (2, 4–5)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4930441" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4930441/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
). 
<collectorName box="[188,205,1558,1581]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">It</collectorName>
has the original labels “Uleåborg” (= 
<collectorName box="[632,692,1557,1582]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Oulu</collectorName>
), “d. 27/7 44”, “ 
<collectorName box="[874,1047,1557,1582]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Coll. Nylander</collectorName>
”, “n. sp.?” and “256.”. 
<collectorName box="[1308,1364,1558,1582]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Type</collectorName>
labels have been added later, including the 
<typeStatus box="[561,659,1593,1618]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">holotype</typeStatus>
label.
</paragraph>
